---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Team — CompTech Lab"
  description="A small senior team of practitioners, structured around depth rather than headcount."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Team</span>
      <h1 class="hero-title">A small senior team. Practitioners, not headcount.</h1>
      <p class="hero-lede">
        CompTech Lab is structured deliberately small. Every engagement is led by a
        practitioner who has done the work before &mdash; not by a partner who sells the
        engagement and then hands it to juniors.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 980px;">
      <article class="prose">
        <h2>How we are structured</h2>
        <p>
          The practice is built around a small group of <strong>senior principals</strong>
          who lead engagements end-to-end. Each principal owns a primary practice area
          (platform, security, AI, data, operations) and depth across two or three adjacent
          areas. We do not separate "sales" from "delivery" &mdash; the practitioner who
          scopes an engagement is the practitioner who runs it.
        </p>
        <p>
          For larger engagements, principals are supported by <strong>specialist
          engineers</strong> brought in for the duration of a workstream &mdash; vetted
          engineers with deep depth in a single area (Cisco fabric, RHACS tuning, identity
          migration, MLOps), who work under the principal's direction and the engagement's
          delivery discipline.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not staff "bench" engineers waiting between engagements. This keeps our
          team senior, keeps overheads low, and keeps customers from paying for staff
          they did not actually need.
        </p>

        <h2>Who you work with</h2>
        <p>
          Every engagement is named at the principal level in the engagement contract.
          You know who is accountable, you can contact them directly, and the principal
          stays engaged from Phase 01 through handover.
        </p>
        <p>
          Principal bios, prior credentials, certifications, and selected client references
          are shared <strong>under NDA during engagement scoping</strong>, not on the
          public website. This is a deliberate choice: it keeps the relationship between
          principal, customer, and prior customer confidential by default, which matters
          to many of our regulated-industry clients.
        </p>

        <h2>How we hire</h2>
        <p>
          Hiring is by reference and depth, not by sourcing pipeline. Principals are
          senior practitioners with prior credentials in their primary practice area
          (typically 10+ years of relevant operating experience) and the kind of writing,
          documentation, and handover discipline this practice is built around.
        </p>
        <p>
          Specialist engineers are brought in for engagements based on a small network of
          vetted practitioners, often through prior working relationships or community
          ties.
        </p>

        <h2>Working with us</h2>
        <p>
          To discuss an engagement, scope a Phase 01, or arrange a leadership-team
          conversation under NDA, contact us via the
          <a href="/contact/">contact form</a> or
          <a href="mailto:hello@comptech-lab.com">hello@comptech-lab.com</a>. We aim to
          respond to substantive enquiries within two business days.
        </p>
      </article>

      <div style="margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem; background: var(--color-dark); color: var(--color-dark-text); border-radius: 0.6rem;">
        <p class="section-eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Request leadership conversation</p>
        <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--color-dark-text-strong); margin: 0 0 1rem; font-size: 1.5rem;">
          Want to meet the principal who would lead your engagement?
        </h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-dark-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 1.5rem;">
          For substantive procurement or pre-engagement discussions, we arrange a video call
          under NDA with the principal who would lead the engagement and any specialist
          engineers relevant to your scope.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Contact us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
